{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-js","path":"/about/","result":{"data":{"wpPage":{"content":"\n<p>This is a blog about my creative technology projects and associated rantings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>My name is Louie Christie and I live in London.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#x2019;m a freelance web developer, coding coach, and underground comedian in my head.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This blog was created around 2008, when I was a young, enthusiastic, gloriously naive graduate spending my time travelling, studying, and making creative projects in technology and media.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At that time I made this blog to document some of that heady period.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then I ran out of money, got jobs,&amp;nbsp;signed non-disclosure agreements, and this blog dried up.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ten years later in 2018, I was made redundant from one of the 90%<sup><a href=\"http://innovationfootprints.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/startup-genome-report-extra-on-premature-scaling.pdf\">*</a></sup> of technology start-up companies that fail, and took the opportunity to blog, be free, freelance, and creative again.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#x2019;m smart, talented, modest, and available for hire.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Feel free to <a href=\"/contact/\">get in touch</a> if you like what you see&#x2026;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:600px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><div aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:36.66666666666667%\"/><img aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/7c6dbe17a455a7a90433e247b56d450d/75985/handwritten_louie_christie_600x220.jpg 150w,\n/static/7c6dbe17a455a7a90433e247b56d450d/f93b5/handwritten_louie_christie_600x220.jpg 300w,\n/static/7c6dbe17a455a7a90433e247b56d450d/b42